The paper deals with the linear complexity of binary sequences, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). It also involves number theory concepts such as Euler quotients and primes, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of decimal sequences to determine the values of k-error linear complexity suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the potential applications of the results in cryptography and security suggest a possible connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
